content.description: There are several climbs on this wall ranging from around 5.5 to 5.9 (they feel harder the lower you start your traverse left--see photo).
content.protection: An easy scramble around back leads to the top where there are boulders for TR anchors.
content.location: This climb is located on Argo Rock's SW face.

content.description: Follow a thin seem through a few horizontals to below the roof. Work your way right around the roof to the top.
content.protection: Cams, Hexes, Stoppers. All gear is horizontal until you go around the corner.
content.location: Start about 5' left of the arete on Argo Rock. North side of crag.

content.description:
Start on the ledge right of Wonder Wall below an overhung block, then fire straight up through classic Annapolis Rock horizontals with a surprising hole on the face 10ft up that makes for a great jug (invisible from below).

 Alternate start at the base of the Wonder Wall to increase the length, beware ledge fall potential though.
content.protection: A couple small cams (BD 0.2-0.5) and a #3 or 4 cam
content.location: Right and above the start of Wander Wall

content.description: A short and sweet classic. Find a discontinuous vertical seam in the middle of the face. Climb up two horizontal ledges, traverse to the left the top out over a big lip.
content.protection: Small to medium sized cams. A short scramble up leads to great TR locations. One small section where pro is tricky/bare, but holds are good.
content.location: The left-most route (facing the rock from below) on the North End.

content.description: climb the face up to the roof below the prominent arete, slam in a piece and make a bouldery move to a jug. casual climbing up the arete from here on out.
content.location: follow the arete to the top and walk off.
